&lt;div class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Account&amp;nbsp; Manager is responsible for the overall satisfaction, health, product usage, and retention of Storable’s Risk partners. This role focuses on proactively identifying and mitigating risk, strengthening long-term relationships, and driving adoption and performance across Storable’s risk products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate has experience managing a portfolio of clients in a SaaS or storage-related environment and excels at building trusted partnerships that create predictable, long-term value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong, long-term relationships with assigned partners&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify, forecast, and manage account risk, including the development and execution of mitigation strategies&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clearly communicate partner needs and risk mitigation requirements across internal teams&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a deep understanding of customers’ businesses, market dynamics, and competitive landscape, and surface meaningful insights to leadership&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify growth opportunities by analyzing product usage, performance trends, and partner needs&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate at-risk accounts as needed and execute retention strategies to reinforce satisfaction and loyalty&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and coordinate client conversations to drive adoption, performance, retention, and upsell opportunities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally to ensure timely resolution of escalated issues and a seamless partner experience&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage CRM and Client Success tools to track engagement, account health, and retention metrics&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years of experience in Client Success, Account Management, or a related role within SaaS or the self-storage industry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with consultative selling and identifying upsell and cross-sell opportunities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong relationship management skills with a proactive, partner-first mindset&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with Client Success platforms and CRM tools (e.g., Vitally, Gong)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized, detail-oriented, and operationally disciplined&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving skills with the ability to assess risk and develop proactive solutions&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated with the ability to operate effectively in a fast-paced environment&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptability to changing priorities, processes, and business needs&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree preferred&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel to client sites and industry events as needed&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Property &amp;amp; Casualty license, or willingness to obtain one&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All applicants must be currently authorized to work in the United States on a full-time basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Storable is a fully distributed company, but is currently only registered for employment in certain states. &lt;/em&gt;To be eligible for employment, you must reside in the following states: &amp;nbsp;AL, AZ, CA, CO, CT, FL, GA, ID, IL, IN, IA, KS, LA, MD, MA, MI, MN, MO, MS, NC, NE, NJ, NV, NY, OH, OK, OR, PA, SC, TN, TX, UT, VA,

&lt;div class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Remote&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Billing Specialist at Storable, you’ll play a key role in our Order to Cash Operations, ensuring that customer orders flow smoothly from quote creation through invoicing and payment collection. Our team supports both upstream Sales Support and downstream Billing &amp;amp; Accounts Receivable operations — together driving accuracy, efficiency, and an excellent customer experience across every stage of the client lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly cross-functional role working across multiple software platforms and partnering with teams such as Sales, Accounting, Client Care, and Implementation. You’ll be trusted to manage complex workflows, maintain data integrity, and contribute to process improvements that make our systems and customer experience better every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do Every Day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate customer data across internal systems (Salesforce, NetSuite, and others).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond promptly and professionally to internal and external inquiries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audit and fulfill requests related to customer orders, accounts, and billing activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to resolve discrepancies or process breakdowns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to process documentation (SOPs) and share feedback for continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in training, pilots, and testing of new tools or workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage workload independently and maintain SLAs for accuracy and responsiveness.&lt;br&gt;Exemplify Storable values through collaboration, integrity, and a customer-first mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus Areas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Support (Order Management)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain client accounts and opportunities in Salesforce with precision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and audit sales opportunities for accuracy and compliance before fulfillment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate order creation, product additions, cancellations, and license transfers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support quoting for new or add-on products, ensuring correct pricing and configurations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with Sales and customers to gather missing or corrected information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure orders are complete, accurate, and closed promptly to enable billing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Billing to ensure timely and accurate invoicing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with data decryptions and archival requests as part of license ownership transfers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Billing (Accounts Receivable)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, issue, and manage both one-time and recurring invoices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate and resolve billing discrepancies or client account issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage customer credits, refunds, and payment updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with clients to resolve past-due balances and support payment setup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain documentation of billing policies, procedures, and methods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze customer accounts and ledgers to ensure accurate reporting and collections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring to the Table&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years in a client-facing billing, order management, or financial operations role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of order-to-cash workflows and customer lifecycle operations.&lt;/li&g

&lt;div class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Development Representative (BDR)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Storable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Storable, we&#39;re redefining property management for specialty real estate. Powered by AI and three decades of industry data, Storable empowers over 33,000 self-storage facilities with the industry&#39;s only fully integrated technology platform. Our end-to-end solutions—from management software and demand generation to CRM tools and delinquency solutions—help storage operators streamline workflows, attract tenants, and grow revenue. Dedicated to empowering self-storage owners and operators, Storable helps you Win More every day. Explore our platform solutions at&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.storable.com/&quot;&gt; storable.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Storable is seeking a Business Development Representative (BDR) to help grow our customer base and deepen relationships with self-storage operators. In this role, you will be on the front lines of our sales motion, connecting with storage facility owners and operators to understand their business challenges and where Storable can make an impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will uncover opportunities across both our existing customer base and net-new prospects, then equip our sales executives with the insights they need to run highly effective demos and sales cycles. By pairing your curiosity and persistence with our industry-leading technology platform, you will play a key role in helping operators modernize their operations and grow their businesses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do every day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage self-storage facility owners and operators via outbound phone, email, and text to understand their business challenges and introduce Storable solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make ~25 highly strategic outbound calls per day, supplemented by additional multi-channel outreach (email, LinkedIn, and other touchpoints) to generate high-quality sales pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualify inbound and outbound leads, uncovering pain points and aligning them to the right products, sales reps, and sales motions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use Salesforce to track activities, manage your pipeline, and capture detailed notes on every customer interaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Account Executives by delivering clear discovery notes and context that set them up for effective demos and proposals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run targeted outbound campaigns to our existing customer base to uncover cross-sell and upsell opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prospect into new regional markets and accounts to create net-new opportunities with storage owners and operators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test and iterate on messaging, value propositions, and outreach tactics, documenting what works so the broader team can adopt it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI-powered tools to research accounts, personalize outreach, and refine messaging to improve connect rates and conversion rates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI and automation within Salesforce and other tools to prioritize your day, streamline follow-ups, and continuously improve your productivity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you need to bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years in SaaS sales or customer-facing support, ideally in a fast-growing environment, or comparable work experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with a CRM such as Salesforce, plus familiarity with tools like Zendesk, Google Workspace, and Microsoft Office.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication skills across phone, email, and text.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong time-management, organization, and multitasking skills, with the ability to simplify and scale your own pr

&lt;div class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Storable is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Business Development Representative&lt;/strong&gt; to help us further grow our customer base. Candidates for this role will be expected to identify and overcome a variety of new hurdles daily. When connecting with storage facility operators, you will shift seamlessly between identifying where we can deliver additional value to our existing customer base and qualifying potential net-new deals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through understanding and identifying what problems self storage operators are facing in their day-to-day operations, you will be able to empower our sales executives with discovery information to help them demonstrate how our technology solutions can help solve those problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly interact with storage facility operators, using Salesforce for team tracking and working purposes. Some of these metrics include (but are not limited to) phone calls, leads, and pipeline management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Constantly test new and innovative approaches to sales and lead generation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate the ability to call out to our current customer base to generate cross-sell opportunities for our sales reps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work multiple outbound/outreach call campaigns from our marketing team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cold-call into regional areas to find net-new opportunities with storage owners&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate the ability to maintain a fun and congenial work environment with your team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, refine, and document various value propositions from scratch to understand how to best route different customers to multiple products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize consistently to move high urgency, high quality opportunities immediately and jump back into next prioritized task&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain strong discipline of clicks and process inside of Salesforce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;More specifically, you will be responsible for:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;80+ outbound calls a day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate 2 outbound SQLs per day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pipeline management and follow-ups with potential clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hitting monthly activity and lead quotas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking detailed notes on all customer interactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years in SaaS sales or support, ideally in a fast-growing startup environment. (Or comparable work experience.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Salesforce (or comparable CRM), Zendesk (or similar tool), Google Apps, and Microsoft Office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A hunger not just to get results right the first time, but also to improve them for the future&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication skills (phone, email, and text)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Time-management skills and motivation to constantly push yourself to do better in a remote environment. You’re comfortable navigating ambiguity, trust yourself to make the right call in the moment, and can calmly develop best practices as you go&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong multitasking and organizational skills, with the ability and foresight to consolidate and simplify your daily tasks in order to scale systems and processes across larger teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with the self-storage industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Salesforce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All applicants must be current

&lt;div class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Success Manager (CSM) - Storage Division (Future Openings)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Storable’s Client Success Team plays a vital role in ensuring our clients achieve measurable business success with our self-storage solutions. As a Client Success Manager (CSM), Senior Client Success Manager (Sr. CSM), or Principal Client Success Manager (Principal CSM) within our Storage division, your level of responsibility and client engagement will scale with experience. Whether managing mid-market clients, high-value accounts, or enterprise relationships, you will drive adoption, mitigate risks, identify growth opportunities, and foster long-term retention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Distinctions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Client Success Manager (CSM): Manages a portfolio of standard to mid-market clients, focusing on adoption, retention, and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Senior Client Success Manager (Sr. CSM): Manages high-value or complex accounts, providing strategic guidance, leading business reviews, and mentoring junior CSMs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Principal Client Success Manager (Principal CSM): Oversees Storable’s largest and most strategic accounts, acting as a trusted advisor to executive stakeholders while influencing internal strategies and mentoring senior team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All Levels:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own client relationships within the self-storage industry, acting as a strategic advisor to drive adoption and expansion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct Business Reviews to reinforce the ROI of Storable’s solutions and align on future strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify upsell and cross-sell opportunities based on business objectives and product fit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor key client metrics, proactively addressing risks and implementing engagement strategies to improve retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a subject matter expert (SME) on self-storage industry trends and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a liaison between clients and internal teams (Product, Engineering, Marketing) to advocate for feature enhancements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize Client Success platforms (e.g., Vitally, Gong) and CRM tools to track engagement and develop data-driven recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Responsibilities by Level&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Success Manager (CSM)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a portfolio of standard to mid-market clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive day-to-day adoption and engagement of Storable’s solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Focus on proactive problem-solving and retention strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal teams to enhance the client experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Client Success Manager (Sr. CSM)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage high-value or complex accounts, acting as a trusted advisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead high-impact Executive Business Reviews, providing strategic insights and ROI assessments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop tailored success strategies that drive client expansion and operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior CSMs, sharing best practices and assisting in complex account situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with leadership on process improvements and contribute to evolving Storable’s Client Success methodology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Principal Client Success Manager (Principal CSM)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee Storable’s largest and most complex clients, ensuring they achieve long-term business success and maximum ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted exec

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a skilled DevOps Engineer with 4+ years of experience in building, automating, and managing scalable infrastructure. The ideal candidate should have strong expertise in Kubernetes, scripting, and a basic understanding of AI/ML workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and manage CI/CD pipelines for application deployment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with containerization and orchestration tools, especially Kubernetes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automate infrastructure provisioning and configuration management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor system performance, reliability, and availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with development and QA teams for seamless releases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot and resolve infrastructure and deployment issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support AI/ML model deployment and basic MLOps workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in DevOps or related roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong hands-on experience with &lt;strong&gt;Kubernetes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in scripting languages such as &lt;strong&gt;Python, Bash, or Shell&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with CI/CD tools (Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of cloud platforms (AWS / Azure / GCP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with containerization tools like Docker&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of Infrastructure as Code (Terraform, CloudFormation, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of AI/ML concepts and model deployment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with MLOps tools and workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with monitoring tools (Prometheus, Grafana, ELK stack)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of security best practices in DevOps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Director, Demand Generation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Director of Demand Generation&lt;/strong&gt; will own the strategy, execution, and performance of Storable’s demand engine for the self-storage vertical. This role is responsible for driving qualified pipelines, improving funnel performance, and accelerating revenue growth across Storable’s Storage platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This leader will operate at both a strategic and operational level by developing scalable demand generation programs while aligning closely with Sales, Product Marketing, and Revenue Operations to ensure marketing efforts translate directly into revenue impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director will bring a strong growth mindset, deep experience building modern B2B SaaS demand engines, and a forward-looking perspective on the role of AI and data-driven marketing in accelerating customer acquisition and lifecycle engagement. This role will report to GM, Storage and serve as the primary owner of demand generation strategy for Storable’s self-storage solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Demand Generation Strategy &amp;amp; Market Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the strategy and performance of Storable’s demand generation engine for the self-storage vertical, driving qualified pipeline and revenue growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build targeted demand generation programs tailored to the self-storage operator ecosystem, including independent operators, regional groups, and multi-location businesses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strengthen Storable’s brand presence and market leadership through integrated campaigns and industry engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a deep understanding of the self-storage landscape, including customer pain points, competitor activity, and emerging market trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Campaign Execution &amp;amp; Lifecycle Marketing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute multi-channel marketing programs across paid media, SEO, lifecycle marketing, digital campaigns, events, and partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop lifecycle marketing strategies that support new customer acquisition, product adoption, and cross-sell opportunities across Storable’s platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Funnel Performance, Analytics &amp;amp; AI Innovation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve funnel performance through continuous optimization of website conversion, landing pages, and digital buyer journeys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage marketing analytics and reporting to evaluate campaign performance, improve marketing ROI, and guide strategic decision making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to apply AI-powered marketing tools and predictive insights to improve campaign targeting, personalization, and demand capture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional GTM Alignment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Sales leadership and Revenue Operations to align marketing initiatives with pipeline targets, sales priorities, and go-to-market strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Product organization to align product roadmaps with market-facing messaging, translating technical milestones into compelling demand generation narratives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Leadership &amp;amp; Industry Presence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and develop a high-performing demand generation team while fostering a culture of experimentation, accountability, and continuous improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Storable’s strategic presence at trade shows and industry events, driving brand visibility, lead capture

