&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Remote&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Storable exists to help Storage, Marine, and RV/Campground operators run better businesses. We began our journey in self-storage and have expanded into Marine and RV/Campground, working toward our vision of being the #1 tech brand in all three verticals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring Sales Executives to own the full B2B sales cycle for our platform, from prospecting and discovery through demo, negotiation, and close. You’ll use a defined, solution-based sales process to understand operator needs and position Storable as a strategic partner that helps them grow revenue and streamline operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll thrive in this role if you are extremely coachable, have a strong desire to be great, and are a self-starter who proactively looks for solutions and learning opportunities. This is a remote role based in the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you&#39;ll do every day&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the full B2B sales cycle from prospecting and first meeting or demo through negotiation and close for self storage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain a healthy pipeline of new-logo opportunities through outbound prospecting, inbound lead follow-up, and partner or marketing-sourced leads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run effective discovery to understand operator goals, diagnose challenges, and position Storable’s solutions with a consultative, value-based approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver compelling demos and presentations to individual stakeholders and cross-functional buying groups at all levels of management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use Salesforce and other sales tools to document activities, track opportunities, and accurately forecast weekly and monthly results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI-powered tools for research, outreach personalization, and pipeline analysis to increase the quality, speed, and impact of your sales activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Sales Leadership, Marketing, and other Sales Executives to refine messaging, share best practices, and continuously improve our go-to-market motions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster strong, trust-based relationships with prospects and customers, ensuring a smooth handoff to post-sales teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on industry, competitive, and product trends so you can act as a knowledgeable advisor to operators across our verticals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Storable at industry events and functions on occasion ( 2-3 times per year), acting as a brand ambassador for our platform. Travel and in person meetings with prospective operators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you need to bring&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of full-cycle B2B sales experience (prospecting through close), ideally in SaaS; adjacent tech-related solutions will also be considered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of new customer acquisition and consistent attainment of or overachievement against revenue targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience selling to multiple levels of management and navigating complex product wheel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in Salesforce (or a similar CRM) to manage pipeline, document activities; Salesforce experience is strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to forecast with accuracy, consistently delivering predictable revenue outcomes through strong pipeline management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extremely coachable, self-motivated, and proactive—eager to seek feedback, learn quickly, and look for solutions and improvements on your own.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to actively listen, tailor your message, and influence outcomes, while leveraging tools (including AI) to improve the quality and efficiency of your work.&lt;/l

&lt;div class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Storable is seeking a Sales Development Representative to help us further grow our customer base. Candidates for this role will be expected to identify and overcome a variety of new hurdles daily. When connecting with marina operators, you will shift seamlessly between identifying where we can deliver additional value to our existing customer base and qualifying potential net-new deals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through understanding and identifying what problems marina operators are facing in their day-to-day operations, you will be able to empower our account executives with discovery information to help them demonstrate how our technology solutions can help solve those problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly interact with marina operators, using Salesforce for team tracking and working purposes. Some of these metrics include (but are not limited to) phone calls, leads, and pipeline management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Constantly test new and innovative approaches to sales and lead generation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate the ability to call out to our current customer base to generate cross-sell opportunities for our account executives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work multiple outbound/outreach call campaigns from our marketing team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cold-call into regional areas to find net-new opportunities with marina owners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate the ability to maintain a fun and congenial work environment with your team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, refine, and document various value propositions from scratch to understand how to best route different customers to multiple products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize consistently to move high urgency, high-quality opportunities immediately and jump back into the next prioritized task.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain strong discipline of clicks and process inside of Salesforce.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;More specifically, you will be responsible for:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;80+ outbound calls a day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate 2 -3 outbound SQLs per day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pipeline management and follow-ups with potential clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hitting monthly activity and lead quotas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking detailed notes on all customer interactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 1 year of experience in high-volume cold calling, consistently achieving or exceeding a target of 80+ calls per day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Salesforce (or comparable CRM), Zendesk (or similar tool), Google Apps, and Microsoft Office.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A hunger not just to get results right the first time, but also to improve them for the future.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication skills (phone, email, and text).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Time-management skills and motivation to constantly push yourself to do better in a remote environment. You’re comfortable navigating ambiguity, trust yourself to make the right call in the moment, and can calmly develop best practices as you go.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong multitasking and organizational skills, with the ability and foresight to consolidate and simplify your daily tasks in order to scale systems and processes across larger teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with the marina or automotive industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Salesforce.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All applicants must be currently authorized to work in the United States on a full-time basis.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
